# What We’re Working on in July 2025

We're keeping things focused this month. Two products, two core objectives: stabilize and scale.

## Tchaikovsky: Beta Access and Feedback Loop

Our AI music platform **Tchaikovsky** officially opened beta access in late June, and July is all about iterating with our first cohort of 50 testers. We're working closely with composers, indie game devs, and YouTube creators to gather real-world feedback on the prompt-to-MIDI system, the web sequencer, and overall performance.

**What we're debugging:**

- Text-to-MIDI edge cases (e.g., complex chord voicings, mixed genres)
- Project autosave reliability
- Browser-based latency with larger arrangements
- Account creation and session management across devices

We're also running daily model regression tests as we refine instrument mapping and velocity dynamics.

## Influent Space: Cleanup and Core Stability

Our second product, **Influent Space**, is undergoing backend and UI stabilization. While it's already live in alpha for IELTS prep, we're now focused on reducing technical debt and preparing the system for upcoming test modules beyond IELTS.

**This month’s targets:**

- Reducing cold start latency for AI evaluation endpoints
- Fixing scoring inconsistencies in speaking module
- Updating classroom permissions for teacher dashboards
- First steps toward multi-test support (TOEFL and Duolingo in R&D)

We're also documenting test logic and writing internal QA tools to automate result validation across speaking, writing, and reading sections.

